		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">Starting stats and learning skills...<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Thu, Aug 17th 10:29 PM2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=3&mid=96656576029157&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=3&mid=96656576029157&num=6&page=&post=1&replyto=96656576029157"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a> | <a class=sm href="/db/journal2.html?user=430"><img src="/shared/user_journal.gif" border="0" height="12" width="17" /> User's Journal</a>   <a name=96656576029157></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=430"><span id=>Geiden</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>6 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.08]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Geiden&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p><br> Most people who start a new monk end up wishing they had put points in one stat rather than in another because they just didnt know what stats were important to a monk. Hopefully the following advice will be helpful to anyone wishing to start a monk.<br><br> There are only two races that can be monks; Humans and Iksar. <br><br> Human Monks have the following stats prior to using bonus points:&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>      STR:80  STA:80  AGI:85  WIS:75  INT:75  CHA:75<br><br> Monks get 20 bonus points to distribute among their stats. If you are playing a Human Monk I'd suggest putting 10 points into STR and the other 10 into AGI. Strength determines how hard you hit as well as how often you hit. Agility determines how often your combat skills (ie, Double Attack, Duel Wield, Block, etc.) are successful as well as determining the rate in which those Combat skills raise in level. <br><br> I would not put points into Dexterity, because 1.) Dexterity raising items are generally fairly cheap and 2.) Dexterity only determines Ranged Attack and the rate an item procs (rate an item's effect goes off in combat). You won't likely be getting any useful weapons that proc until well into your teens or twenties so I wouldn't worry about that right away. I wouldn't put skills into Stamina because every 2 points put into the stat supposedly results in 1 additional HP. While the extra HP's will definitely help in the newbie levels, at higher levels you'd much rather not get hit than try to soak damage. I'd definitely choose the AGI over the STA.<br><br> Iksar Monks have the following stats prior to spending bonus points:<br>       STR:75  STA:75  AGI:100  DEX:95  WIS:80  INT:75  CHA:55<br><br> In the case of the Iksar I'd put all of my points into Strength. The starting Agility is already 100 and thats quite good to start with. I'd avoid the other stats due to the same reasons as above.<br><br>  Should any new monks have questions or elder monks wish to comment please feel free to email. I believe all of the information on how the stats work to be accurate, but should anyone have proof otherwise please correct me.<br><br> Geiden</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br> "I like a man who grins when he fights..."<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;                                   - Winston Churchil</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >6 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 4:21 AM2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=3&mid=96656576029157&num=6&page=&post=1&replyto=96658690319802"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=96658690319802></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.85]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p><br>This advice is given for a human monk, I have never had a iksar monk so I can't comment on that.<br><br>Agility will determine how often your defensive combat skills like block, dodge, etc... will proc and also determines your base ac.&nbsp;&nbsp;Therefore agi is obviously a very important stat for monks because of the lack of hit points they have.  Also, at low lvls, 1 or 2 ac isn't much, but at higher lvls you notice it, believe it or not.  Another small piece of advice about agi...I see alot of young monks going for agi instead of ac equipment.  I must say that I made this mistake when I was younger too but then I realized, ac equipment will yeild better results than agi equipment will.  If you don't believe me, try it out and see for yourself.  I'm not saying you should scrap agi, agi is still a important stat, just don't neglect ac for it.  I suggest putting half of your skills into agi.<br><br>Dex determines how often your offensive combat skills proc, how often your weapon effects proc, and is supposed to determine how often you hit, (although I have never noticed a difference).  I would put maybe 1/3 of your remaining points into this.  I put half of mine in it and I am regretting it now.<br><br>Finally we come to strength.  Str for monks means one thing and one thing only, how hard you hit for.  The damage that monks can deliver is based in quick, fast, strikes for low amounts of damage, therefore when you increase str, you increase the amount of damage than each one of these strikes can do.  That is a significant increase in total damage and any monk that wishes to remain the king of undisputed melee damage would be wise to put at least, the remaining 2/3 of your points into str.  <br><br>Of course, there are individual cases where you may wish to distribute your points a little differently.  This is just my take on how to distribute your points.  I made my monk with half agi and half dex.  Now I wish I had more str instead of dex.<br><br>Zanshin Wuitang<br>35 monk prexus</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
