		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.11]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>A most informative primer, Geiden, and your points are well taken.&nbsp;&nbsp;I also recommend the allocation of all character creation points into the Strength attribute, with specific reference to those creating Iksar monks. <br><br>The possession of strength in the savage land of Kunark increases a young broodling's chances of survival, and coupled with the innate agility and dexterity of a markedly superior reptilian form, one will find themself growing swiftly in power and experience.  The secret and seldom travelled path to true strength and wisdom lies in the knowledge of one's own abilities... and limitations.  Risk and challenge beyond one's abilities serve only to vanquish the foolhardy.<br><br>Within the realms of knowledge and skill,  my advice is this.  Seek out the counsel of your brothers and sisters of the Way, for experience is the greatest teacher.  Those who follow the chosen Path travel by different routes, and their actions will have proven to them the most prudent skills to choose.  Learn from their teachings, yet the decisions are yours alone to make.  Retain always in your mind the strongest aspect of a monk:  reliance on the self.  Magicks and other such trappings should serve only to bolster the skills already in your possession.    <br><br>A monk is strong in body and in mind, in thought and in action.  Little else is of concern to you.  A spartan existence is conducive to the cultivation of a tranquil mind.  Build your strength from within, and it will fill your entire being.<br><br>Soliok Iarrascurath<br>Vallon Zek server<br>(guild inquiries welcome)<br><br><br>One must be blind to see<br>The wisdom within all things<br><br> </p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
